post_cb({"26785827": {"CommentCount": "3", "ViewCount": "99", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "2069064", "CreationDate": "2014-11-06T17:37:53.000", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-06T17:51:15.260", "Title": "When is (*b) false?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "26785861", "LastEditDate": "2014-11-06T17:45:41.583", "Id": "26785827", "Score": "-1", "Body": "<p>I am just playing around with pointers, and I have a question. </p>\n<p>I wrote the following while loop:</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n\n    int a = 10;\n    int *b = &amp;a;\n\n    while(*b){ cout &lt;&lt; \"true\"; break; }\n\n    cout &lt;&lt; endl;\n    cout &lt;&lt; b;\n\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>When will the condition, (*b) be false? If I don't point it to a value, the code simply doesn't compile.</p>\n<p>Also, how whould you translate that conditional test to english? </p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "2993456", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "26785980": {"ParentId": "26785827", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Condition in the statement</p>\n<pre><code>while(*b){ cout &lt;&lt; \"true\"; break; }\n</code></pre>\n<p>can be translated in English the following way</p>\n<pre><code>while(*b not_eq 0 ){ cout &lt;&lt; \"true\"; break; }\n</code></pre>\n<p>where <code>not_eq</code> corresponds to English words <code>not equal</code>.:) This statement with <code>not_eq</code> shall be compiled if you have a modern compiler.</p>\n<p>Take into account that in this particular case <code>*b</code> is equal to <code>10</code>, because <code>b</code> points to <code>a</code></p>\n<p>You could write the loop the following way</p>\n<pre><code>while ( *b not_eq 0 ){ cout &lt;&lt; \"true\"; b = 0; }\n</code></pre>\n<p>that is without the break statement. The effect would be the same.</p>\n<p>According to the C++ Standard</p>\n<p>4.12 Boolean conversions [conv.bool]</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_26785827_26785980_0\">1 A prvalue of arithmetic, unscoped enumeration, pointer, or pointer\n  to member type can be converted to a prvalue of type bool. A zero\n  value, null pointer value, or null member pointer value is converted\n  to false; any other value is converted to true.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2877241", "LastEditorUserId": "2877241", "LastEditDate": "2014-11-06T17:51:15.260", "Id": "26785980", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2014-11-06T17:45:47.613", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-06T17:51:15.260"}, "26785861": {"ParentId": "26785827", "CommentCount": "6", "Body": "<p>In this code it would only be false if <code>a</code> is zero.  It's not, so the condition will never be false.</p>\n<p><code>*b</code> dereferences the pointer <code>b</code> and evaluates as the pointed-to value. Since <code>b</code> points to <code>a</code>, it will always be true that <code>*b == a</code> (unless you change <code>b</code> to point somewhere else).</p>\n<p>The English translation of <code>while (*b)</code> is \"execute the body of this loop as long as the object <code>b</code> points to evaluates as true.\"  An <code>int</code> is true when its value is non-zero.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "501250", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "26785861", "Score": "7", "CreationDate": "2014-11-06T17:39:08.693", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-06T17:39:08.693"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_26785827_26785980_0": {"section_id": 44, "quality": 1.0, "length": 28}}, "n3337": {"so_26785827_26785980_0": {"section_id": 41, "quality": 1.0, "length": 28}}, "n4659": {"so_26785827_26785980_0": {"section_id": 45, "quality": 1.0, "length": 28}}}});